  "issue_title": "gitt miner post: JSON output collapses no_response into rejected",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n`gitt miner post` (`gittensor/cli/miner_commands/post.py`) renders three response categories in human mode but only two in JSON mode, silently collapsing `no_response` into `rejected`. This is the same JSON/human-parity bug class that #724 just fixed in the sibling `gitt miner check` command \u2014 the same shared-helper pattern applies directly.\n\n## The mismatch\n\nThe synapse exposes three distinct response states: `accepted=True`, `accepted=False`, and `accepted=None` (validator unreachable / no response).\n\n**Human mode** (`post.py:158-164`) renders them as three separate categories:\n\n```python\nif r['accepted'] is True:    status = '[green]\u2713[/green]'      # accepted\nelif r['accepted'] is False: status = '[red]\u2717[/red]'         # rejected\nelse:                        status = '[yellow]\u2014[/yellow]'   # no response\n```\n\n**JSON mode** (`post.py:138-150`) emits only two buckets:\n\n```python\n{\n    'success': accepted_count > 0,\n    'total_validators': len(results),\n    'accepted': accepted_count,\n    'rejected': len(results) - accepted_count,   # silently includes no_response\n    'results': results,\n}\n```\n\nSo a run with 2 accepts, 1 reject, and 2 no-responses shows `2 \u2713 / 1 \u2717 / 2 \u2014` to humans but reports `accepted: 2, rejected: 3` in JSON. JSON consumers cannot distinguish \"validator rejected my PAT\" from \"validator unreachable\" \u2014 two operationally different conditions that need different follow-up.\n\n## Suggested fix (mirror of #724)\n\n#724 solved the identical bug class in `gitt miner check` by extracting two shared helpers in `gittensor/cli/miner_commands/helpers.py`:\n\n- `_pat_check_row_category(row)` \u2014 single source of truth for category classification\n- `_pat_check_aggregate_counts(results)` \u2014 Counter-based bucketing both modes consume\n\nThe same shape applies here:\n\n1. Add `_pat_post_row_category(row)` with three buckets: `accepted`, `rejected`, `no_response`.\n2. Add `_pat_post_aggregate_counts(results)` returning `{'accepted': N, 'rejected': N, 'no_response': N}`.\n3. Update `post.py` so both renderings consume the helpers (`**counts` spread in JSON; `_PAT_POST_STATUS_MARKUP[category]` lookup in the table).\n4. Add unit tests in `tests/cli/test_miner_commands.py` mirroring `TestPatCheckAggregateCounts`.\n\nAfter the fix the JSON output shape becomes:\n\n```python\n{\n    'success': counts['accepted'] > 0,\n    'total_validators': len(results),\n    **counts,                              # accepted / rejected / no_response\n    'results': results,\n}\n```\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-01T18:45:56.000Z",
